page.title: 04The Train Station
page.content: The station was built in 1902.There are three or four trains an hour in the rush-hour and forty or fifty trains a week each way,going to places like High Wycombe,Princess Risborough,Little Kimble,Gerrards Cross and Ruislip. The bridge on the station that goes from one platform to the other,was just being mended by putting a new roof on it.They did have one before but it started to collapse.So they took it apart and put it back together again. The types of people who come to the station are mostly commuters(which are working people)and housewives taking their children out for the day.The station is at its buisiest time in the morning because of all the commuters, but dies down at 11.00.There is a bike shed which costs 30p a day and 16 pounds 50p a year.
